  "text": "This constraint mainly refers to the similarity degree of two codes and the similarity degree of shift position of two given codes in the same direction. It primarily is aimed to make each code not similar with other code. It generally is divided into two aspects: Continuous and discontinuous similarities. For example, AGTGTAATGGGG andACGCCTATGGGA have the same continuity 5 from the 7th base to the 11th base is subcode ATGGG. The discontinuous similarity is 6. The mathematical definition of this measurement [CITATION_1] is:",
